1.
OVERVIEW
Your right to privacy and the protection of your personal data is important to us. Giggle Academy is committed to the best practices in privacy and we will only collect data when it’s strictly necessary to provide our services.
Giggle Academy aims to be a free, interactive and adaptive online education platform focused on providing basic education (grades 1-12) to underprivileged children.
The information accessed will vary based on our relationship or interaction with you.
By using Giggle Academy and our Services, including downloading one of our mobile applications, visiting our website and participating in our campaigns, you acknowledge the use, disclosure, and procedures outlined in this Privacy Notice.
The following sections provide further details as to how we process your personal information through Giggle Academy.
2.
CHILDREN
At Giggle Academy, we prioritize the privacy of children and are dedicated to protecting their personal information. Our App and Services are designed to put parents and guardians in control. Children under 16 can use the Service without providing contact information. Any areas of the Service which require providing personal information are made available only to adults and protected by a Parental Gate, as further described below.
Parents are in control. To ensure proper use of our App by children, we require parental approval. Only adult is allowed to create and manage the child’s account, install the App, and submit the necessary information.
·
To create an account for a child, an adult must first register with a parent account and create the child’s profile name and the child’s year of birth or school grade for content personalization.
·
Once the account is set up, we only collect the information necessary for the child to fully participate in the educational activities offered by our Services. We do not ask for more information than what is required for the child’s use of the Services.
·
Parents retain the choice to give appropriate permission such as device’s microphone, camera, location services, push notification.
·
Parents can update, correct, and delete your account information through your account settings.
·
Additionally, we use a Parental Gate to prevent children from disclosing personal information online. This feature includes a knowledge-based quiz or an age check or passcode to verify that the user is an adult.
·
No third party tracking and no targeted advertising. We take steps to avoid the collection of information for behavioral or targeted advertising purposes when we believe the Service is being used by students or children.
We value the privacy of both children and their adult, who are responsible for their child’s data. This Privacy Policy aims to clarify how we handle a child’s personal information during their use of our Service.
